──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Third-party material
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

HelixOS does not vendor any third-party source code. Every line in
src/ and include/ was written for this project.

Build-time tools used (none redistributed):

  * GNU Binutils       — GPL v3+
  * GNU GCC            — GPL v3 with libgcc runtime exception
  * NASM               — 2-clause BSD
  * GNU GRUB           — GPL v3+
  * QEMU               — GPL v2+

These are obtained from your system package manager or built from
official source by scripts/build-toolchain.sh; they are not bundled
into the HelixOS binary or distributed with it.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Architectural patterns
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The boot path, IDT setup pattern, and PIC remap sequence are common
knowledge in x86 kernel development. The OSDev wiki (wiki.osdev.org)
and James Molloy's "Roll your own toy UNIX-clone OS" tutorial were
consulted for invariants and ordering; no code was copied. See
AUTHORS.md for full acknowledgements.

